Oakville first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Oakville had a population of 49. The population density was {{convert|36.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Oakville was 24 (49%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 1 (2%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 12 (24%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 11 (22%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 25 persons (51%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Oakville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0653196 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 30, 2025}}</ref>

There were 29 households, and the average household size was 1.69. The median age was 51.5{{nbsp}}years.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 37 housing units, of which 29 (78%) were occupied. Of these, 8 (28%) were owner-occupied, and 21 (72%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

